title: Sabrina Carpenter's New Music Video Has A 'Girl Meets World' Nod
text:
Sabrina Carpenter's New Music Video Has A 'Girl Meets World' Nod That subway car sure looks familiar ... 02/10/2017 12:04 pm ET Minou Clark Associate Editor of News and Emerging Platforms, The Huffington Post 
“ Girl Meets World ” star and rising pop singer Sabrina Carpenter just dropped the music video for her song “Thumbs.” 
The finger-snapping tune is the second single off of Carpenter’s album “Evolution,” which came out in October 2016. After its release as a single in January, “Thumbs” hit pop radio’s Top 40 . #ThumbsMusicVideo is out now!! what are u still doing reading this https://t.co/mo13eUayBl — Sabrina Carpenter (@SabrinaAnnLynn) February 10, 2017 
The entire video takes place in a subway car, with Carpenter looking sassier than ever. If you’re a “ Girl Meets World ” fan you probably recognize a similar subway from the show’s set. YouTube/Sabrina Carpenter 
Keep sashaying around that subway car, girl. We’ll just keep praying “Girl Meets World” gets picked up by Netflix for another season.
